President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the renewal of the appointment of Mr Kayode Pitan as the Managing Director of the Bank of Industry (BOI) for a final term of five years. In a statement issued on Tuesday by the Special Assistant on Media to the Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Ifedayo Sayo, the new appointment which takes effect from May 27, 2022, was conveyed via a letter signed by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr Boss Mustapha and dated March 11, 2022. Also, the president approved the renewal of the appointment of Alhaji Dikko Aliyu Abdulrahaman as part – time chairman of the bank for a final term of five years with effect from May 27, 2022. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE ‘Officials initially offered to help but when the number of able-bodied citizens at the centre increased, they left us unattended to’
